(Reading chat) Sangha 6: "As the restoration happens or reorientation, what does this change, if anything, about Bodhicitta?"

Dawai: Oh, that's a good inquiry. The world looks distorted from within the ripples of the waters. Reorientation brings us into the whole lake, so we are no longer hypnotized or confined by the ripples.

Bodhicitta, Bodhi meaning enlightened, Citta meaning mind, the lake has always been Bodhicitta. We tend to get lost in the ripples, the energy, the expression of the lake, and in that way get lost in the expression of our minds. These are our eggshells. We grow up in expressions of our minds, not a bad thing, it just happens. There's nothing to do, nothing to judge.

Once the eggshells of energetic constructs, the nirmāṇakāya confinement, begin to mature, we come into the wholeness of our mind, not just the energetic expression. Cognition is always infused with energy. We get caught up in energy, someone points to cognition, and suddenly we hold the energy, less turbulent. That's ultimate, ultimate Bodhicitta.


